to the editor both your nov 5 news article and a nov 6 letter about the new difficulties of conducting political polls in the age of cellphones and caller id do not mention one extremely important point the need of professional social scientists to conduct polls polls are a vital tool for political scientists and sociologists who seek to understand and explain how and why groups of people think act and believe as they do randomly selected individuals who are contacted for brief interviews serve as the backbone to provide accurate raw data for our studies of political behavior whatever one 's opinion of polls used for strictly partisan political purposes the new difficulties encountered in collecting poll data and in reaching the american public lessen our understanding of the mechanics and motivations of political action leaving every citizen the poorer nathan a paxton cambridge mass nov 6 2002

